            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2314-Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rip the<strong> ciabatta roll<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>ripped ciabatta</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>golden</strong> <strong>croutons</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2314-Step-4-x200.jpg",
